Test file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts
Failing test: "should kill a live cell with more than 3 neighbors (overpopulation)"
Expected behavior: A cross/plus pattern where center has 4 neighbors (dies) and dead corners have 3 neighbors (come alive via reproduction)
Input: [[false,true,false],[true,true,true],[false,true,false]]
Expected: [[true,false,true],[false,false,false],[true,false,true]]
Current error: AssertionError: expected [[false,true,false],[true,false,true],[false,true,false]] to deeply equal [[true,false,true],[false,false,false],[true,false,true]]
Implementation file: src/game-of-life.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const countNeighbors = (grid: boolean[][], row: number, col: number): number => {
  let count = 0;
  for (let r = row - 1; r <= row + 1; r++) {
    for (let c = col - 1; c <= col + 1; c++) {
      if (r === row && c === col) continue;
      if (r >= 0 && r < grid.length && c >= 0 && c < grid[r].length) {
        if (grid[r][c]) count++;
      }
    }
  }
  return count;
};

const cellSurvives = (isAlive: boolean, neighborCount: number): boolean =>
  isAlive ? neighborCount === 2 || neighborCount === 3 : false;

export function nextGeneration(grid: boolean[][]): boolean[][] {
  if (grid.length === 1 && grid[0].length === 1) return [[]];
  return grid.map((row, rowIndex) =>
    row.map((cell, colIndex) =>
      cellSurvives(cell, countNeighbors(grid, rowIndex, colIndex))
    )
  );
}
```

The issue is that `cellSurvives` always returns `false` for dead cells. Dead cells with exactly 3 neighbors should come alive (reproduction rule). Fix `cellSurvives` to also handle reproduction: dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive.

Previous tests that must still pass:
- nextGeneration([]) === []
- nextGeneration([[true]]) === [[]]  (single cell, 0 neighbors - special case)
- nextGeneration([[true, true]]) === [[false, false]]  (1 neighbor each, dies)
- nextGeneration([[true,true],[true,true]]) === [[true,true],[true,true]]  (3 neighbors each, survives)

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

